Aristides, surnamed the Just, had a con- siderable Share in the Victories of Mara- thon and Salamis. He was Commander in Chief at the Battle of Plataea, in which Mardonius, the Perfian General, was killed and his Army routed. Yet however eminently distinguished for his military Abilities, we should rather con- sider him as a great Example of all civil Virtues.
